    "name": "focus_chain",
    "description": "",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "OBJECT",
      "properties": {},
      "required": []
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "generate_explanation",
    "description": "Opens a multi-file diff view and generates AI-powered inline comments explaining the changes between two git references. Use this tool to help users understand code changes from git commits, pull requests, branches, or any git refs. The tool uses git to retrieve file contents and displays a side-by-side diff view with explanatory comments.",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "OBJECT",
      "properties": {
        "title": {
          "type": "STRING"
        },
        "from_ref": {
          "type": "STRING"
        },
        "to_ref": {
          "type": "STRING"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "title",
        "from_ref"
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "trigger_nordic_action",
    "description": "Execute commands in the nRF Connect terminal with correct Nordic/Zephyr environment. ALWAYS use this for west, nrfjprog, nrfutil commands.\n\nBOARD NAME FORMAT (REQUIRED):\n  • nrf52840dk/nrf52840 (NOT just \"nrf52840dk\")\n  • Find name: west boards | grep <chip>\n\nPROCESS CLEANUP (Crucial for stability):\n  • Before separate/new task: pkill -9 JLink; pkill -9 nrfutil; sleep 1\n  • PREVENT HANGS: Use \"timeout 60s\" for blocking commands (e.g. timeout 60s west flash)\n\nFORBIDDEN COMMANDS (WASTEFUL/FLAKY):\n  • DO NOT USE: hcitool, nRFConnectScanner, ble-scan (Host scanning fails in containers)\n  • DO NOT USE: nrfjprog --family (Use --ids instead)\n  • DO NOT USE: nrfjprog --info (Use --ids instead)\n\nVERIFICATION STRATEGY (TRUST THE LOGS):\n  1. PRIMARY: RTT or UART logs showing boot & functionality.\n  2. SECONDARY: Ask user (\"Do you see LED blinking?\").\n  3. NEVER scan from the host machine.\n\nRTT LOGGING (THE \"PERFECT\" SEQUENCE):\n  1. Check RTT enabled: grep CONFIG_USE_SEGGER_RTT prj.conf\n  2. Cleanup: pkill -9 JLink; pkill -9 nrfutil; sleep 1\n  3. Connect: Use \"nRF RTT Terminal\" (VS Code) or JLinkExe (Plan B)\n  4. RESET (Crucial): In a NEW terminal, run: nrfjprog --reset -s <serial>\n  5. Observe: Watch RTT terminal immediately to catch boot logs\n  6. MISSING LOGS? Check prj.conf for CONFIG_LOG_DEFAULT_LEVEL=4 (Debug)\n\nUART LOGGING (If RTT disabled / CONFIG_LOG_BACKEND_UART=y):\n  • \"RESET & CAT\" PATTERN (Run in new terminal):\n    timeout 20s sh -c 'nrfjprog --reset -s <SN> && sleep 1 && cat /dev/ttyACM0'\n\nFLASH PRIORITY:\n  1. Get devices: nrfjprog --ids\n  2. ONE device: timeout 60s west flash\n  3. MULTIPLE: timeout 60s west flash --snr <serial>\n  4. RECOVER: nrfjprog --recover (only if flash fails)\n\nBUILD DECISION TREE:\n  1. Check for build folder: ls build/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"no build\"\n  2. If NO build/: west build -b BOARD .\n  3. If build/ EXISTS:\n     - Fresh rebuild: west build -b BOARD . -p always\n     - Incremental: west build\n",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "OBJECT",
      "properties": {
        "action": {
          "type": "STRING"
        },
        "command": {
          "type": "STRING"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "action",
        "command"
      ]
    }
  },
